# Legality Validation

When building or modifying Pokemon teams, **do not read** `data/legal/pokemon.txt`, `items.txt`, or `learnsets.json` to check legality -- this will cost a lot of tokens. Instead, use the CLI helper:

## Quick single-Pokemon check

```bash
python scripts/check_team_legality.py \
  --pokemon "Charizard" --item "Charizardite Y" \
  --moves "Heat Wave,Protect,Air Slash,Solar Beam"
```

## Full team check (Showdown paste via stdin)

```bash
echo 'Charizard @ Charizardite Y
- Heat Wave
- Protect
- Air Slash
- Solar Beam

Venusaur @ Lum Berry
- Protect
- Sleep Powder
- Giga Drain
- Sludge Bomb' | python scripts/check_team_legality.py
```

## Full team check (from file)

```bash
python scripts/check_team_legality.py --file team.txt
```

## What it validates

- Species against `data/legal/pokemon.txt` (~195 legal species)
- Items against `data/legal/items.txt` (~120 legal items, mostly Mega Stones + berries + type boosters)
- Moves against `data/legal/learnsets.json` (per-species learnsets; `moves.txt` is **ignored**)
- Species clause (no duplicate species) and item clause (no duplicate items)

## Exit codes

- `0` — all checks passed
- `1` — at least one violation found
- `2` — bad input / no Pokemon found

## Key legal-pool facts (to avoid common mistakes)

- **No Life Orb, Assault Vest, Damp Rock, Choice Band, Choice Specs** — the item pool is restricted
- **Choice Scarf** is legal; most other Choice items are not
- Always use `learnsets.json` as the move source of truth
- Mega Stones have Champions-specific names (e.g. `Meganiumite`, `Chimechite`, `Dragoninite`)
